routes.documentation: Returns different parameters based on "type" parameter (VIRTUAL_ROOM, PHYSICAL_RESOURCE, ROOM_CAPACITY).

Additional data: authorizedData (Look inside RoomController > handleListRoomData), allocation and executableState (listing all returns only overall state which you can get by calling ReservationRequestState.fromApi(reservationRequest)), childRequests - these are request made due to periodicity, history - these are requests that moidify the parent request (find more in DetailReservationRequestController > handleDetailReservationRequestTab), periodicity - repeating of reservation (look inside ReservationRequestModel)

routes.documentation: Takes partial JSON data to update participant.
Rooms are reservation requests scheduled by a scheduler, they become executables after scheduling.
Returns list of SystemPermission that requesting user has
